Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
i think living in a dormitory as a freshman is a very important experience for two main reasons. it builds community and instills a sense of pride about your college. commuter students often do not have many relationships and are not deeply rooted to their alma mater for life.